    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="216" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 14,
                            1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith for your information copy
                        of an agreement<note n="*" xml:id="d216fn1">See <ref target="#pg_158">page
                                158</ref>.</note> between the Government of the United States and
                        the Imperial Government of Russia for a modus vivendi in relation to the
                        fur-seal fisheries in Bering Sea and the North Pacific Ocean, concluded on
                        May 4, 1894.</p>
                <p>I also inclose translation of a note of the 4th instant<note n="†" xml:id="d216fn2">See <ref target="#pg_190">page 190</ref>.</note> from
                        the Russian minister in this capital, wherein he declares that the Imperial
                        Government is prepared to negotiate and sign with the United States,
                        England, Mid Japan a treaty, in virtue of which the principles and
                        regulations of the Paris Tribunal of Arbitration shall be applicable,
                        indifferently, to all the waters of the Pacific Ocean situated north of the.
                        thirty-fifth parallel of north latitude.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. F. Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
